SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 74
BY SENATORS LAMBERT AND PRICE AND REPRESENTATIVES BACALA,
BRASS, EDMONSTON AND WILEY
CONDOLENCES. Expresses condolences upon the passing of former Senator Louis J.
Lambert Jr.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the passing of
3 former State Senator Louis Joseph Lambert Jr., and to record the legislature's
4 enduring appreciation for his distinguished public service to the state of Louisiana.
5 WHEREAS, it is with deep regret and profound sorrow that the Legislature of
6 Louisiana has learned of the passing of former State Senator Louis Joseph Lambert Jr.; and
7 WHEREAS, Louis Joseph Lambert Jr. was born on December 21, 1940, in DeRidder,
8 Louisiana, to Louis Joseph Lambert Sr. and Roberta Richardson Lambert while his father
9 was working on a seismic crew for an oil company; and
10 WHEREAS, shortly after his birth, the Lambert family returned to Sorrento, where
11 they could trace their Acadian heritage back to the earliest settlers of Ascension and
12 Livingston parishes during the late 1700s; and
13 WHEREAS, as a young child, Senator Lambert spent many hours in his grandfather's
14 small grocery store in Sorrento; and
15 WHEREAS, while listening to his grandfather interact with the grocery store
16 customers and discuss matters of the day he developed his keen interest in politics; and
17 WHEREAS, as a resident of Ascension Parish he devoted his life to public service,
18 civic leadership, and the advancement of the people of Louisiana; and
