1 WHEREAS, Senator Lambert's early achievements included attaining the rank of
2 Eagle Scout, serving as a page in both the Louisiana Legislature and the United States
3 Congress, and graduating at the top of his Congressional page school class in 1958; and
4 WHEREAS, Louis earned a Bachelor of Arts in political science from Louisiana
5 State University and a Juris Doctor from Loyola University in New Orleans, and later, in
6 1968, established a respected law practice in Gonzales, Louisiana; and
7 WHEREAS, Senator Lambert was first elected to the Louisiana Senate in 1972, and
8 two years later, to the Louisiana Public Service Commission, where he served for eighteen
9 years and was widely recognized as a steadfast advocate for Louisiana consumers; and
10 WHEREAS, in 1979, he was the Democratic nominee for governor of the State of
11 Louisiana, participating in one of the closest gubernatorial elections in modern state history;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, Senator Lambert returned to the Louisiana Senate in 1994 and served
14 with distinction, culminating in his tenure as Senate President Pro Tempore from 2000 to
15 2004; and
16 WHEREAS, he was a champion for education and authored legislation creating the
17 River Parishes Community College, a lasting contribution to the region he represented; and
18 WHEREAS, Senator Lambert was also chairman of the Senate Committee on
19 Environmental Quality, and worked collaboratively to advance environmental stewardship,
20 later becoming a member of the Louisiana State University Board of Supervisors, where he
21 continued his commitment to higher education; and
22 WHEREAS, in recognition of his decades of leadership and public service, Senator
23 Lambert was inducted into the Louisiana Political Hall of Fame in 2024; and
24 WHEREAS, Senator Lambert was a devoted husband, father, and grandfather, a man
25 of deep faith, and mentor to countless young leaders, lawyers, and public servants, and his
26 passing has left a void in the hearts of his family, friends, colleagues, and the many citizens
27 whose lives he touched throughout his public service; and
28 WHEREAS, he is preceded in death by his parents, Louis J. Lambert Sr. and Roberta
29 Lambert; his brother, Billy Lambert; and his grandson, Hunter Louis Lambert; and he is
30 survived by his cherished wife of fifty-nine years, Mary Smith Lambert; his sister, Edana
